==Finnish==
===Verb (profane)===

#''Vituttaa''

The vord ''vituttaa'' is one of a few Finnish verbs that in their basic form already describe an on-going thing, and can include the person experiencing the thing. ''Vituttaa'' means roughly "is deeply annoyed", and if no other person is indicated, in most cases it applies to the user of the word. Therefore "mua vituttaa" means the same, literally "I'm deeply annoyed".

The on-going status of being deeply annoyed, is called [[vitutus]].

Derived from [[vittu]].

===Words with similar properties===

''Panettaa'' "is craving to fuck" derived from ''[[panna]]'' "To fuck"

''Hirvittää'' "is horrified". Derived from ''hirveä'' "horrible".

